\cref{fig:change_beta_dcs_mnist,fig:change_beta_dcs_cifar10,fig:change_beta_dcs_nuswide} show the change of the ranking results with the change of $\beta$. Overall the relative rankings are not significantly impacted by $\beta$, demonstrating the stableness of the comparison results among various defenses. As $\beta$ grows to large values, e.g. $\geq 0.9$, the metric places overly strong weight on MP, resulting in more variations on the rankings. Specifically, dCor ranks higher with the increase of $\beta$ thanks to its better MP preservation at the cost of a weaker AP limitation.
